IN the past Easter Weekend, Tshakhuma Tsha Madzivhandila and Black Leopards players were spotted taking part in the Easter games in Polokwane. The DStv Premiership players represented different teams at the Thabiso Semenya Annual Easter Tournament which took place at Moletjie Mashobohleng sports ground. The four days tournament saw PSL starts such as Lefa Hlongwane, Tebogo Makobela and Onyedikachi Ononogbu who are all playing for Leopards being part of the games dishing out Kasi flavor. Former Kaizer Chiefs midfielder Joseph Malongoane was also among those players who graced the tournament. Take a look at other players who played the amateur tournament. 